Workflow

User performs a gesture.

Motion sensor captures acceleration and rotation data.

Sensor data is sent to the microcontroller.

TinyML model processes the data and classifies the gesture.

Gesture information is encoded using FSK.

The signal is transmitted to the receiver.

Receiver decodes the signal and displays the message.

